There were 3 of us and we went for an early dinner.  Somewhere around 8pm.  The wait wasn't too long before we were seated.  It's a very small tapas place, but it gave us an opportunity to meet this sweet couple from Australia.  When we walked in we saw some tapas that interested us then we also ordered off the menu.  We ordered a few from the bar area.Potatoes with sausageOlives with AnchoviesWe also ordered the HamManchego CheeseSpanish Tortillaand the House Cava of course.  Great time at a great restaurant.
